<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - technology]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/technology <atom:link href="http://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/technology" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - technology - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 7 月 19 日星期三 17:15:01 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Juul Has a New High-Tech Vape and Hopes the FDA Won’t Ban It]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>该设备具有年龄验证功能，并且只有一种口味——弗吉尼亚烟草<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066869"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819926?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Juul 正在寻求 FDA 授权在美国销售这款下一代设备</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Juul 实验室</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066869"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jennifer-maloney" itemprop="url" rel="author">詹妮弗·马洛尼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日中午 12:00 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/juul-has-a-new-high-tech-vape-and-hopes-the-fda-wont-ban-it-655bd16a"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Juul Labs 正在寻求美国对下一代蒸发器的授权，而这家电子烟制造商则在等待其当前产品是否可以留在市场上的消息。</p><p>该公司表示，Juul 的新设备已在英国和加拿大上市，具有年龄验证功能，可防止使用假冒或未经授权的第三方补充墨盒。 Juul 本周向美国食品和药物管理局提交的最新申请仅包括一种口味——弗吉尼亚烟草——尼古丁浓度为每毫升 18 毫克，与 Juul 在英国和加拿大销售的浓度相同。</p><p> Juul 表示，其新设备的申请避免了去年导致 FDA 下令 Juul 现有产品<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-the-fda-banned-juul-e-cigarettes-11666374991?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">退出市场的</a>技术问题，这一裁决使该公司陷入了困境，并将<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/juul-secures-financing-to-avoid-bankruptcy-plans-to-cut-30-of-jobs-11668097803?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其推向破产的边缘</a>。 FDA 禁止了 Juul 的产品，因为 Juul 没有充分回答该机构关于该公司在其原始蒸发器留在市场的申请中提交的毒理学数据的问题。在该公司提出上诉期间，FDA 暂停了该禁令。上诉仍在审理中。 Juul 告诉 FDA，该机构悬而未决的问题本来可以通过“一个电话”得到解决。</p><p> Juul 表示，尚未决定是否以 Juul 品牌或其他名称销售这款新型蒸发器。</p><p>所有电子烟制造商都必须向 FDA 提交新电子烟产品的审查，然后才能在美国销售。 Juul 表示，该公司本周提交了科学研究，以证明其新设备与原来的电子烟产品一样，使用户接触到的致癌物质比香烟少，而且帮助成年吸烟者转向更安全的替代品的好处超过了让年轻人沉迷于尼古丁的潜在危害。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819929?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Juul 表示，其新设备的申请避免了去年导致 FDA 下令 Juul 现有产品退出市场的技术问题。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的尼克·哈根</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Juul 表示，它希望这款新设备能够吸引那些尝试过但拒绝其他电子烟或从未尝试过其他电子烟的成年吸烟者，这种设备每次抽吸时会产生更多的气雾，并更稳定地输送尼古丁。</p><p> Juul 一直在对其他口味进行研究，以提交给 FDA，包括薄荷醇和将烟草或薄荷醇与果味相结合的复杂口味。在英国，Juul 销售复杂的口味，例如含有苹果香料的秋季烟草。 Juul 的新填充盒可以配置为薄荷醇或其他口味的版本必须由经过年龄验证的用户在使用前解锁——这一功能旨在减轻监管机构对儿童和青少年中流行口味的担忧。</p><p> Juul 表示，它正在对 FDA 提交的文件采取“瞄准目标”的方法，向监管机构展示一系列产品，希望至少其中一些产品能够通过审查。</p><p> Juul 首席产品官柯克·菲尔普斯 (Kirk Phelps) 表示：“我们针对两个公共卫生问题设计了一种技术解决方案：改善成年吸烟者从可燃香烟的戒烟情况，并限制未成年人接触电子烟产品。”</p><p> Juul 的新设备无法与假冒或未经授权的 Juul 兼容补充盒配合使用，几年前，当这些补充盒充斥着吸引儿童的水果口味时，这成为监管机构的一个问题。附带的应用程序允许电子烟用户跟踪他们的使用情况和设备的位置。 Juul 表示，该应用程序捕获的个人使用数据将保密，公司不会收集。</p><p>该公司表示，新设备具有更好的温度控制功能，可以最大程度地减少气溶胶中有毒物质的存在。 Juul 表示，它仍在研究新设备每吸一口可产生多少尼古丁，以及与市场上其他电子烟产品相比如何。 Juul 表示，该装置每次抽吸时产生的尼古丁含量比传统香烟要少。</p><p> Juul 的研究包括一项在英国首次购买新设备后对约 100 名吸烟者进行为期六个月的跟踪研究。在六个月内，近 33% 的人已从香烟转向 Juul 设备。</p><p> 2018 年，当 Juul 时尚的电子烟<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/juul-tried-to-position-itself-as-a-responsible-actor-it-backfired-11569193666?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">成为青少年身份的象征</a>， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/youth-use-of-e-cigarettes-jumped-78-government-study-shows-1542310284?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">未成年人吸电子烟数量激增时，</a>美国监管机构开始严厉打击电子烟市场。此后，青少年对电子烟的使用以及 Juul 在年轻人中的受欢迎程度有所下降。现在吸电子烟的中学生和高中生更喜欢 Elf Bar 等一次性品牌。</p><p>写信给詹妮弗·马洛尼 (Jennifer Maloney)： <a href="mailto:Jennifer.Maloney@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Jennifer.Maloney@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/juul-has-a-new-high-tech-vape-and-hopes-the-fda-wont-ban-it-655bd16a</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/juul-has-a-new-high-tech-vape-and-hopes-the-fda-wont-ban-it-655bd16a<author><![CDATA[Jennifer Maloney]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>专有的</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>电子烟</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>电子烟</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Netflix Scraps Its Cheapest Ad-Free Plan]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国和英国的新客户不再适用每月 9.99 美元的基本计划<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066853"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819960?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Netflix 最便宜的无广告套餐现在新会员每月 15.49 美元。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Gabby Jones/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066853"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joseph-pisani" itemprop="url" rel="author">约瑟夫·皮萨尼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 11:46（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-scraps-its-cheapest-ad-free-plan-aea36bb7"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="company-name">Netflix</a>已停止提供最便宜的不播放广告的套餐。</p><p>这家流媒体公司周三表示，不再为美国和英国的新客户提供每月 9.99 美元的基本套餐。 Netflix 表示，现有订阅者只要不更改或取消该套餐，就可以继续使用该套餐。</p><p>该公司最便宜的无广告套餐现在新会员每月 15.49 美元。</p><p>自去年推出以来，Netflix 一直试图让更多人加入<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-pitches-advertisers-as-ad-tier-trails-smaller-rivals-dd394ffb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">其每月 6.99 美元的广告播放计划</a>。这些客户为每个会员带来的收入比其基本和标准计划更多，因为 Netflix 通过广告和每月订阅费赚钱。</p><p> Netflix 在周三的一份声明中表示，广告支持的计划“鉴于我们目录的广度和质量，为消费者提供了巨大的价值。”</p><p>今年早些时候，Netflix 开始认真<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-password-sharing-crackdown-families-e5e97e69?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">打击密码共享行为</a>，杜绝贪图便宜者。那些想要继续共享帐户的人必须每月额外支付 7.99 美元。</p><p> Netflix 预计将于周三下午发布第二季度财报。</p><p>写信给约瑟夫·皮萨尼 (Joseph Pisani)： <a href="mailto:joseph.pisani@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joseph.pisani@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/751c4a60-884a-4f29-9ce6-db91fbb92c01.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 15:46:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-scraps-its-cheapest-ad-free-plan-aea36bb7</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/netflix-scraps-its-cheapest-ad-free-plan-aea36bb7<author><![CDATA[Joseph Pisani]]></author><category> WSJSpeeddesk</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Netflix</category><category> NFLX</category><category>多媒体内容服务</category><category>媒体内容分发</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>流媒体服务</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Let’s All Start Leaving Voicemails Again]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>新的来电筛选工具和语音备忘录意味着是时候再次发声了<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819484/?width=2000&amp;size=1.949" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>图片由 ELENA SCOTTI/《华尔街日报》绘制，ISTOCK<span>图片由 ELENA SCOTTI/《华尔街日报》绘制，ISTOCK</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064532"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064532"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="columnist_mini"> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joanna-stern"><img width="45" height="45" src="https://si.wsj.net/public/resources/images/BN-SE117_STERN__A_20170219231355.jpg" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></a></div><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/joanna-stern" itemprop="url" rel="author">乔安娜·斯特恩</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 11:34（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/voicemail-apple-iphone-call-screening-2d2fa77f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p><em>不要挂断！您已到达乔安娜·斯特恩 (Joanna Stern) 语音信箱的盛大重新开放。听到提示音后，请说出您的名字以及为什么我应该立即接听。是的，我可能会像 1995 年一样筛选电话。祝你有美好的一天！</em></p><p>多年来，朋友、同事和诈骗者在到达我的语音信箱时都会收到“此邮箱已满”的信息。现在，我已经录制了新的问候语并清理了混乱的内容，因为语音邮件又回来了！</p><p>我的意思是，如果我们愿意的话。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apple-ios-17-features-b7dde486?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">苹果即将推出的 iOS 17</a>具有新的呼叫筛选功能“实时语音邮件”，可在呼叫者离开时为您提供语音邮件的实时文本记录。您甚至可以中途接听消息。这就是<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ria37d9mInY" target="_blank" class="icon none">老式答录机</a>的所有乐趣，但没有微型磁带。 （iOS 17 上周发布了公开测试版，预计将于 9 月发布。） </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819336?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在 iOS 17 通话屏幕中，您可以快速将人们发送到语音邮件，然后查看实时转录。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔安娜·斯特恩/华尔街日报</p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          inline
"></div><p>非常棒。只有一个问题：我们几年前就停止留下和检查语音消息。现在，发短信“给我打电话”比“等等，请尽快给我回电话”更有效。</p><p>哎呀， <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/adrianalopez/2014/07/31/new-sexy-world-of-call-centers-help-small-businesses-increase-sales-significantly/?sh=5f0d6698767b" target="_blank" class="icon none">早在 2014 年</a>，80% 的来电者就没有留言，因为他们认为自己的声音不会被听到。我找不到更多最新的统计数据，可能是因为民意调查机构找不到任何语音邮件用户进行民意调查。</p><p>为了让语音信箱卷土重来，我们必须使用语音信箱。我认为我们应该这样做。是的，我听到你们怀疑：“<em>当然</em>，让我们一边清理传真机上的灰尘吧！”但请听我说完——在嘟嘟声之后。</p><h3> 1.技术很酷。</h3><p>当我第一次在编辑打来的电话中使用实时语音邮件时，它让我有点惊讶。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/dice/stern0719-voicemail-901edb96-a232-43a0-acc7-84deaf08d54f/inset.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>像大多数日子一样，我忽略了他的电话。但这一次，他留下了一条信息。当他开始讲话时，他的话的实时转录就打印在通话屏幕上。我能够接起电话并开始与他交谈， <strong>&nbsp;</strong>语音信箱中间。</p><p>我的编辑希望我接电话，但我姐姐不知道接下来会发生什么。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="">苹果</a>在 iOS 17 中默认的机器人问候语是：“在提示音后<span class="company-name-type">，</span>请说出您打电话的原因。您试图联系的人可能会接听。”只是没有任何语气。 （告诉过你，这是测试版。）所以她只是坐在那里等待，等待嘟嘟声。我新的个性化问候解决了这个困惑。</p><p>专业提示：旧的呼叫筛选借口（“刚走进房子”、“我妈妈在另一条线路上”）在这个互联时代不再起作用，因为电话几乎可以跟随你走到任何地方。</p><p>任何使用过苹果常规语音邮件转录功能的人都知道，其语音到文本的翻译有时可能会让人印象深刻。 （我还在嘲笑<a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jason-gay?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">杰森·盖伊</a>最近给我留下的一条消息的转录：“我有足够的时间说话”，实际上是“我告诉你和我说话。”）实时语音邮件也有类似的问题。尽管如此，你还是可以很好地理解所说的内容——而且为了笑声，这是值得的。另外，即使您在通话中接听，您也可以返回并收听录音。</p><p> Android 并没有完全相当于实时语音邮件的功能，尽管 Google 的 Pixel 确实有一个<a href="https://support.google.com/phoneapp/answer/9118387?hl=en" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">可以为您筛选呼叫</a>的自动助理。</p><h3> 2. 声音就是连接。</h3><p>我非常相信电话。来回发短信会让人迷失很多东西，而<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/stop-with-the-video-chats-already-just-make-a-voice-call-11622034001?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">视频通话可能会让人迷失太多</a>。一条简单的语音消息可以传达大量的意义和感觉。</p><p>是的，我把这些<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/voice-messages-phone-etiquette-guide-11664388240?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">文本聊天音频消息</a>混为一谈。对于十几岁或二十多岁的人来说——他们从未听到过忙音——语音留言实际上只是不同名称的语音邮件。它们非常受欢迎。 <a href="https://blog.whatsapp.com/making-voice-messages-better" target="_blank" class="icon none">WhatsApp 称每天发送的信息有 70 亿条</a>。在 iOS 17 中，苹果还为语音消息添加了文本转录功能。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="489" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819343?width=700&amp;height=489" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在 iOS 17 中，消息中的语音注释会自动转录为文本。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔安娜·斯特恩/华尔街日报</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>德克萨斯大学奥斯汀分校市场营销和心理学助理教授阿米特·库马尔（Amit Kumar）研究了语音与文本通信，他说：“声音带有所谓的副语言线索，例如语调、音高变化，可以以文本无法传达的方式传达情感。”</p><p>虽然库马尔没有专门研究语音邮件和语音备忘录，但他告诉我，当我们选择文本而不是语音时，我们就失去了建立更紧密联系的机会。</p><h3> 3.你比垃圾邮件更好。</h3><p>在当今的世界里，我们的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sorry-i-missed-your-text-messaging-is-the-new-email-11661917283?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">短信就是新的电子邮件</a>，我们的通话记录里堆满了机器人呼叫者，人声可以打破混乱。 （希望这不是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/i-cloned-myself-with-ai-she-fooled-my-bank-and-my-family-356bd1a3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人工智能克隆</a>！）</p><p> YouMail 是一款提供语音邮件以及针对机器人电话和机器人短信的保护的应用程序，其首席执行官亚历克斯·奎利奇 (Alex Quilici) 表示，越来越多的实际与之开展业务的公司都采取了这种策略。他告诉我，当你听到真人说话时，“你更有可能注意那个语音邮件。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>你听过语音信箱吗？什么会让您再次使用语音信箱？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>其中一些新工具有助于处理垃圾邮件。 <a href="https://www.youmail.com/" target="_blank" class="icon none">YouMail 的 Android 和 iOS 应用程序</a>限制自动呼叫者拨打您的手机并在您的语音信箱中弹出。苹果的实时语音邮件也是如此。该公司表示，运营商识别为垃圾邮件的电话会立即被拒绝，并且不会被实时转录。</p><p> iOS 17 中还有另一个技巧。您可以通过打开“静音未知来电者”来筛选不在您的地址簿中的任何非垃圾邮件来电者，无论是医生办公室、随机工作联系人还是无来电显示号码。通过软件更新，它现在可以将这些呼叫者直接路由到实时语音邮件。如果他们开始留言，您可以对其进行筛选。但是，是的，这是一个很大的“如果”。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="381" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819340?width=700&amp;height=381" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">如果您不喜欢，可以在 iOS 17 设置中关闭实时语音邮件。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：未注明出处</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>因此，深吸一口气，给朋友或同事打电话，带回趋势。得了吧，我们这样做了三十多年了。您的声音（邮件）很重要。</p><p> <em>—</em> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/newsletters?sub=486&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none"><em>在此注册《乔安娜·斯特恩的科技事》</em></a> <em>，这是一份新的每周通讯。现在一切都是科技的事情。专栏作家乔安娜·斯特恩 (Joanna Stern) 是您的向导，为您提供有关我们始终互联的世界的分析并回答您的问题。</em></p><p>写信给乔安娜·斯特恩： <a href="mailto:joanna.stern@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">joanna.stern@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/8eb76449-c0ed-4ed2-99d6-c872a430fac3.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 15:34:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/voicemail-apple-iphone-call-screening-2d2fa77f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/voicemail-apple-iphone-call-screening-2d2fa77f<author><![CDATA[Joanna Stern]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>系统软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>电信服务</category><category>无线电信服务</category><category>移动通讯</category><category>手机/移动电话</category><category>通讯软件</category><category>计算</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>移动设备</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>网络电话</category><category>生物识别技术</category><category>技术</category><category>语音识别软件</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>苹果</category><category>AAPL</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>个人技术</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>系统软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>电信设备</category><category>个人电子产品</category><category>电信服务</category><category>无线电信服务</category><category>移动电信</category><category>细胞</category><category>手机</category><category>通讯软件</category><category>计算</category><category>移动设备</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>网络电话</category><category>生物识别技术</category><category>技术</category><category>语音识别软件</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft, Activision Blizzard Extend $75 Billion Merger Deadline]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>延期至 10 月中旬，使这些公司有更多时间获得英国监管部门的批准<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066278"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="531" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819836?width=860&amp;height=531" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">魔兽世界系列是动视暴雪庞大视频游戏组合的一部分。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美国商业资讯/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066278"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sarah-e-needleman" itemprop="url" rel="author">莎拉·E·尼德曼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 11:02（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-and-activision-blizzard-extend-75-billion-merger-deadline-6d0556b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">微软</a>和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/ATVI" class="company-name">动视暴雪</a>表示，他们已同意将 750 亿美元合并的最后期限延长至 10 月中旬，此举将使他们能够继续努力获得英国监管部门的批准</p><p>两家公司原计划在周二之前完成交易，但现在要求在 10 月 18 日之前完成一项交易，这将使微软拥有动视暴雪庞大的视频游戏组合，其中包括<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-microsofts-75-billion-bid-for-activision-blizzard-hinges-on-call-of-duty-e86df589?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">《使命召唤》、</a> 《糖果粉碎传奇》和《魔兽世界》等热门系列的游戏。</p><p>两家公司同意，如果交易在 8 月 29 日之后终止，则终止费从 30 亿美元增加到 35 亿美元；如果交易在 9 月 15 日之后取消，则终止费从 30 亿美元增加到 45 亿美元。</p><p>微软副主席兼总裁布拉德·史密斯<a href="https://twitter.com/BradSmi/status/1681650463022931968" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">在推特上表示</a>，延期将为解决剩余的监管问题提供“充足的时间”。他表示：“我们对完成这笔交易的前景充满信心。”</p><p>动视暴雪的发言人回应了史密斯关于交易迅速完成的言论。</p><p>动视暴雪还发布了第二季度财务业绩，收入同比增长 34%，达到 22.1 亿美元。盈利增长了一倍多，达到 5.87 亿美元，净预订量增长了 50%。微软预计将于周二公布季度业绩。</p><p>动视补充说，其董事会批准了 99 美分的股息，将于 8 月 17 日支付。该公司上次支付 47 美分的年度股息是在 2022 年 4 月。</p><p>由于投资者押注交易更有可能完成，动视暴雪股价最近上涨。周二收盘价为 92.74 美元，7 月份上涨 10%。交易价格为每股 95 美元。</p><p>周三早盘交易中，动视暴雪股价下跌 0.4%，而微软股价则持平。</p><p>微软于 2022 年 1 月宣布计划收购动视暴雪，在对视频游戏发行商的净现金进行调整后，这笔交易的估值为 690 亿美元。这些公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsofts-75-billion-activision-blizzard-deal-gets-eu-approval-116b7d9a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在欧洲、中国和其他市场获得了监管部门的批准</a>，但在美国和英国遇到了障碍。</p><p>上周，一名美国联邦法官驳回了联邦贸易委员会阻止该交易的请求，同时该机构对初审法院法官<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-activision-blizzard-deal-ftc-hearing-d42675f1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">7 月 11 日的裁决</a>提出上诉。如果法官驳回禁令，联邦贸易委员会通常会放弃对交易的反对意见， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Meta Platforms</a>收购<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ftc-abandons-challenge-to-metas-acquisition-of-virtual-reality-startup-6ee5e767?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">虚拟现实公司 Within Unlimited</a>时就发生了这种情况。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=81754EB5-BC43-42BD-909C-41E7CB3DE1A4&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fmicrosoft-and-activision-blizzard-extend-75-billion-merger-deadline-6d0556b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">联邦法官周二裁定，微软可以完成以 750 亿美元收购动视暴雪的交易。该裁决意味着美国目前对两家公司的合并不存在任何障碍。照片：Richard B. Levine/Zuma Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>英国竞争和市场管理局现在是交易完成的唯一主要障碍。监管机构表示，担心此次合并可能会损害新兴的云游戏市场或互联网上的视频游戏流媒体市场，尽管上周它同意考虑<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsofts-court-win-puts-u-k-regulator-in-challenging-spot-over-activision-deal-a6e95963?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对收购进行重组</a>。英国监管机构补充说，需要对所做的任何改变进行新的调查，但没有透露需要多长时间。</p><p>通过收购动视暴雪，微软希望加强其在移动游戏领域的有限影响力，按收入计算，移动游戏是迄今为止视频游戏行业中最大的部门。这家软件巨头还希望为其视频游戏订阅服务 Game Pass 充实其游戏组合，其中包括云游戏。</p><p>完成与动视的交易对于微软实现这些目标至关重要。在中国以外，微软可能收购的拥有大量产品组合的游戏公司屈指可数。</p><p>为了在过去 18 个月里吸引监管机构，微软与<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NTDOY" class="">任天堂</a><span class="company-name-type">、</span><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NVDA" class="company-name">英伟达</a>和其他竞争对手<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-signs-call-of-duty-pact-with-nintendo-as-activision-deal-faces-scrutiny-77f47443?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">达成协议</a>，让《使命召唤》——游戏行业最受欢迎的系列游戏之一——在 10 年内可供玩家在其平台上平等使用。周日，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SONY" class="">索尼集团</a><span class="company-name-type">，</span></p>此次收购的最大批评者之一也<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/call-of-duty-will-stay-on-playstation-after-microsoft-activision-deal-34b8ebb1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">同意同样的安排</a>。<p></p><p>如果微软能够突破最后的障碍并完成交易，此次收购将提振其视频游戏业务，并标志着微软战胜对大型科技交易审查更加严格的机构的努力取得了胜利。</p><p>写信给 Sarah E. Needleman，邮箱为<a href="mailto:Sarah.Needleman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Sarah.Needleman@wsj.com</a></p><p id="correction" class="correction"><strong>更正和放大</strong><br>微软和动视暴雪同意，如果交易在 8 月 29 日之后终止，终止费将增加到 35 亿美元。本文的早期版本错误地表示，如果交易在 8 月 29 日之前终止，终止费将增加到 35 亿美元。（7 月 19 日更正）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 15:02:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-and-activision-blizzard-extend-75-billion-merger-deadline-6d0556b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-and-activision-blizzard-extend-75-billion-merger-deadline-6d0556b<author><![CDATA[Sarah E. Needleman]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>玩具/游戏</category><category>消费品</category><category>计算</category><category>游戏软件</category><category>休闲/旅游用品</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购/合并/持股</category><category>收购/合并</category><category>企业行动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>兼并</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>动视暴雪</category><category>动车组</category><category>微软</category><category>微软公司</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>所有权变更</category><category>收购</category><category>合并</category><category>持股</category><category>企业行动</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>玩具</category><category>游戏</category><category>消费品</category><category>计算</category><category>游戏软件</category><category>闲暇</category><category>旅游用品</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Jailed Crypto Tycoon’s Company Appoints CEO]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Terraform Labs 聘请 Chris Amani 管理公司，联合创始人面临欺诈指控<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064824"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819557?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Chris Amani 此前曾担任 Terraform 的首席运营官和首席财务官。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Terraform 实验室</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064824"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alexander-osipovich" itemprop="url" rel="author">亚历山大·奥西波维奇</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 10:46（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jailed-crypto-tycoon-do-kwons-company-appoints-new-ceo-d58fa058"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Terraform Labs 任命了一位新首席执行官来运营这家加密货币公司，而其联合创始人 Do Kwon 因<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/crash-of-terrausd-shakes-crypto-there-was-a-run-on-the-bank-11652371839?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">TerraUSD 和 Luna 加密货币</a>价值 400 亿美元的暴跌而面临欺诈指控。</p><p> Terraform Labs 告诉《华尔街日报》，临时首席执行官是 Chris Amani，他曾担任该公司的首席运营官和首席财务官。</p><p> Terraform Labs 试图表明，当该公司前首席执行官在巴尔干国家黑山入狱时，一切照常进行。美国和权的祖国韩国都<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-south-korea-vie-over-extradition-of-crypto-fugitive-do-kwon-738923fc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在寻求引渡他</a>。</p><p>该公司正在加紧努力，以复兴支撑失败的加密货币的 Terra 区块链。阿玛尼表示，该公司将开发“提供真正实用性”的应用程序，并将在未来几个月分享其计划的更多细节。</p><p>阿玛尼在接受采访时表示：“我们对如何挽救这一局面有一个愿景，尽管我认为这会很困难并且需要很长时间。”</p><p> Amani 表示，该公司拥有约 40 名员工，其中约 15 名员工在 2022 年 5 月 TerraUSD 和 Luna 崩盘之前就在 Terraform Labs 工作。</p><p>该公司在一份声明中表示，Kwon 于 3 月 31 日辞去了新加坡 Terraform Labs 首席执行官的职务，大约<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/crypto-fugitive-do-kwon-arrested-in-montenegro-minister-says-18e58f31?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在他被捕一周后</a>。 Terraform Labs 表示，他于 5 月 27 日辞去公司董事职务，专注于“个人法律事务”。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> “我们希望他能做到最好，并希望他能够洗清所有指控。但是，尽管他被监禁并且面临着自己的法律挑战，但我们在没有他的情况下继续前进是有意义的，”阿玛尼说。</p><p> Amani 证实，Kwon 仍然是 Terraform Labs 的大股东。美国证券交易委员会在法庭文件中表示，权拥有该公司 92% 的股份。</p><p>阿玛尼说，权在被捕前半年从公众视野中消失后，继续远程运营 Terraform 实验室。官员称，权在三月中旬进入邻国黑山之前一直在塞尔维亚藏身。</p><p> SEC 在 2 月份对 Terraform Labs 和 Kwon 提起<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fugitive-stablecoin-founder-do-kwon-accused-of-securities-fraud-in-u-s-6da8f781?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">民事欺诈诉讼</a>，指控他们误导 TerraUSD 和 Luna 的投资者。该公司的律师试图驳回诉讼，称该机构超越了其权限。权否认犯有欺诈行为，并在美国检察官提起的相关刑事案件中受到指控。</p><p> Amani 是美国人，居住在美国。他曾担任商业软件初创公司 Humanity 的首席执行官，然后于 2021 年 12 月加入 Terraform Labs 担任首席运营官。后来他又增加了首席财务官的头衔。</p><p>经历了 TerraUSD 崩盘的经历后，Amani 表示 Terraform Labs 不会寻求推出新的稳定币。</p><p> TerraUSD 是一种所谓的算法稳定币，它利用金融工程将价格维持在 1 美元，而无需在银行持有实际美元来支撑其价值。</p><p> Kwon 将 TerraUSD 吹捧为货币的未来，投资者蜂拥而入，主要是受到将资金存放在稳定币中的人获得近 20% 收益率的承诺所吸引。 2022 年 5 月的几天里，TerraUSD 跌破 1 美元，而其姐妹加密货币 Luna 暴跌超过 99%。这次崩盘耗尽了全球数千名投资者的积蓄。</p><p>纽约联邦检察官指控权先生因倒闭而犯有八项欺诈刑事罪。权先生的律师尚未对刑事指控做出正式回应，除非他被引渡到美国，否则不太可能做出回应</p><p>与此同时，韩国指控权先生违反其资本市场法。 Terraform Labs 称韩国的指控不公平且“高度政治化”。</p><p>写信给亚历山大·奥西波维奇： <a href="mailto:alexo@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">alexo@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/6b1a689f-8207-40db-aa97-c22b0bc8a24d.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 14:46:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jailed-crypto-tycoon-do-kwons-company-appoints-new-ceo-d58fa058</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jailed-crypto-tycoon-do-kwons-company-appoints-new-ceo-d58fa058<author><![CDATA[Alexander Osipovich]]></author><category>华尔街日报财经</category><category>华尔街日报金融市场</category><category>银行/信贷</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>技术</category><category>虚拟货币/加密货币</category><category>企业犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>管理</category><category>管理层变动</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>克里斯·阿玛尼</category><category>道权</category><category>企业犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>管理</category><category>管理举措</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>高层管理人员</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>欺诈罪</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>银行业</category><category>信用</category><category>金融服务</category><category>金融科技</category><category>技术</category><category>虚拟货币</category><category>加密货币</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft to Offer Some Cybersecurity Free After Suspected China Hack]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>该公司表示将通过成本较低的云服务向客户提供安全日志<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065271"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819653?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">在涉嫌中国网络间谍活动后，微软的分层支付系统招致批评。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Victor J. Blue/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065271"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dustin-volz" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯汀·沃尔兹 (Dustin Volz)</a></span> ，华盛顿； <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/robert-mcmillan" itemprop="url" rel="author">罗伯特·麦克米伦 (Robert McMillan)</a></span> ，旧金山</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 10:24（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-to-offer-some-cybersecurity-tools-free-after-suspected-china-hack-6db94221"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">微软</a>表示，继上周披露了与<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-email-hack-shows-greater-sophistication-skill-of-chinas-cyberspies-7f7cff67?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国黑客</a>有关的重大安全漏洞（一些客户无法检测到）后，该公司计划免费提供一些可以发现网络攻击的工具。</p><p>在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="">微软</a><span class="company-name-type">的</span>分层支付系统因涉嫌中国网络间谍活动而受到批评之后，微软决定开放其记录云活动的后端系统。该公司表示，这些活动渗透了其基于云的电子邮件系统，并破坏了全球约两打组织的收件箱。美国官员称，包括国务院官员和商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多在内的联邦政府是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-hackers-spied-on-state-department-13a09f03?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">此次袭击的受害者</a>之一。</p><p>微软安全副总裁 Vasu Jakkal 表示，从 9 月份开始，这家科技公司将向该公司低成本云服务的被许可人免费提供 31 个极其重要的安全日志，其中包括用于识别与中国有关的攻击的电子邮件日志类型。 Jakkal 表示，该公司还将安全日志的保留期限从 90 天增加到 180 天。</p><p>虽然日志不能防止网络攻击，但公司可以使用它们来检测和调查黑客行为，因为日志会跟踪 Microsoft 服务器上的活动。官员上周表示，在最近与中国有关的漏洞中，检测攻击所需的关键日志信息仅向微软顶级 Microsoft 365 云服务（称为 E5）的购买者开放。这使得一些<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-hacking-was-undetectable-for-some-who-had-less-expensive-microsoft-services-58730629?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拥有更便宜套餐的客户</a>无法确定他们是否遭到了黑客攻击。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>美国网络安全和基础设施安全局网络安全执行助理主任埃里克·戈尔茨坦 (Eric Goldstein) 表示：“这是确保每个微软客户都有正确的可见性来检测我们每天针对美国组织的其他威胁的重要一步。”</p><p>贾卡尔和戈尔茨坦表示，识别有价值的安全日志并将其免费提供给微软客户的努力已经持续了一年，这是微软和拜登政府合作的结果。两人都拒绝将周三的声明直接与所谓的中国黑客事件联系起来。但“鉴于地形的复杂性，显然迫切需要完成这项工作，”贾卡尔说。</p><p>黑客攻击事件发生后，拜登政府高级官员、一位著名的民主党参议员和网络安全专家呼吁微软更广泛地提供云上活动的计算机日志。一旦微软意识到这一黑客活动（该活动首先由国务院发现），即使目标公司没有支付高级服务费用，它也能够识别受害者。但专家表示，一些客户缺乏可见性，这意味着这次攻击可能会在较长一段时间内未被注意到。</p><p>网络安全顾问杰克·威廉姆斯表示，许多公司没有意识到他们的云计算产品可能带有不完整的日志。威廉姆斯说：“我定期咨询组织，只有当他们必须调查帐户接管时，他们才会发现他们丢失了这些日志。”</p><p>俄勒冈州民主党参议员罗恩·怀登(Ron Wyden)对此举表示欢迎，但表示，像微软这样的大型网络安全企业的激励措施不一致，导致提供不安全的产品并向客户追加销售网络安全附加产品利润丰厚。</p><p>怀登在一份声明中表示：“微软不应该对联邦系统进行多次灾难性的黑客攻击，才为政府客户制定基本的安全功能标准，但迟做总比不做好。” “展望未来，联邦机构应该坚持要求软件合同包括安全日志和其他网络安全功能，这样我们的国家安全就不会再因劣质采购流程而受到损害。”</p><p>微软表示，在所谓的中国泄露事件中，该事件可以追溯到 5 月份，并在大约一个月后被发现。政府官员表示，他们担心微软低成本云产品的一些用户无法看到揭露泄露事件的电子邮件记录信息。</p><p>微软仍在继续调查最近涉嫌的中国数据泄露事件，但迄今为止该公司尚未解释黑客是如何成功实施这一事件的。戈尔茨坦周二表示，联邦政府正在继续调查此次黑客攻击并了解其全面影响。官员们尚未正式将这次袭击与北京联系起来，但表示他们没有理由怀疑微软的攻击行为。中国否认了这些指控，并指责美国进行普遍的网络间谍活动。</p><p> “这是一次复杂的攻击，我们正在与微软密切合作，调查仍在继续，”戈德斯坦说。</p><p>写信给达斯汀·沃尔兹 ( <a href="mailto:dustin.volz@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dustin.volz@wsj.com)</a>和罗伯特·麦克米兰 (Robert McMillan) ( <a href="mailto:robert.mcmillan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">robert.mcmillan@wsj.com)</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 14:24:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-to-offer-some-cybersecurity-tools-free-after-suspected-china-hack-6db94221</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-to-offer-some-cybersecurity-tools-free-after-suspected-china-hack-6db94221<author><![CDATA[Dustin VolzRobert McMillan]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>计算机/消费电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>计算机服务</category><category>云计算</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>计算</category><category>数据服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>市场/营销</category><category>使用/消耗统计</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>隐私问题/信息安全</category><category>网络犯罪/黑客攻击</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>微软</category><category>微软公司</category><category>瓦苏·贾卡尔</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>市场</category><category>营销</category><category>用法</category><category>消费统计</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>隐私问题</category><category>信息安全</category><category>网络犯罪</category><category>黑客攻击</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电脑</category><category>消费类电子产品</category><category>软件</category><category>应用软件</category><category>计算机服务</category><category>云计算</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>计算</category><category>数据服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[How a Whisper Network for Online Dating Turned Divisive]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Facebook 经历了一年的快速增长后，为保护女性而成立的私人团体在如何前进方面存在分歧<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817715/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> 《华尔街日报》的埃里克·卡特。 <span>《华尔街日报》杂志埃里克·卡特。杂志</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066115"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066115"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sara-ashley-obrien" itemprop="url" rel="author">萨拉·阿什利·奥布莱恩</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 19 日上午 10:07 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/are-we-dating-the-same-guy-facebook-groups-2c7d3009"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p>这些群组一年多前开始出现在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/META" class="company-name">Facebook</a>上。他们将自己描述为女性的安全空间，旨在向“可能是骗子、骗子、虐待者”或其他“有毒”的男性发出警报。很快，全国各地的女性都在当地发布了“我们在和同一个人约会吗？”的帖子。群组——描述他们在约会应用程序上匹配的男性，或者询问其他人的情报。</p><p>但随着会员数量猛增，这些私人耳语网络发现自己陷入了身份危机。版主正在努力执行该组织关于发布和共享信息的规则。 （所描述的男性的名字和照片是允许的，但向群组外的人发送屏幕截图是不允许的。）男性正在向 Facebook 的母公司 Meta 提出删除请求，并建立自己的群组，而一些女性则表示，她们只是来喝“茶”的——关于她们所在城市的男性的八卦。</p><p>第一个团体于 2022 年 3 月在纽约市为女性成立，目前拥有 113,000 名成员。另一个位于达拉斯-沃斯堡的工厂拥有 120,000 名员工。全世界有超过 150 个“我们约会同一个人吗”群组，以及十几个审核政策较为宽松的“未经审查”版本。但这些旨在保护人们的论坛对于许多人来说已经变成了更像娱乐的东西，而对于另一些人来说，则是一种祸害。</p><h3>没有屏幕截图，没有姓氏，没有诽谤</h3><p>2005 年，一位名叫 Tasha Cunningham 的女士创办了一个名为 DontDateHimGirl.com 的在线论坛。成员们分享了他们以老式方式（例如在酒吧和通过朋友）认识的男人的战争故事，以及在 Match.com 和 JDate 等早期约会网站上遇到的男人的故事。</p><p>坎宁安说，在鼎盛时期，DontDateHimGirl.com 吸引了大约 100 万会员，但她决定在 2010 年关闭该网站。她说，该论坛上曾写到过来自男性的法律威胁，她正试图专注于独立的商业投资。</p><p>坎宁安说：“这对我个人来说有点太过分了，我决定放弃这一点。”</p><p> 2012 年 Tinder 的出现彻底改变了在线约会，同时也带来了新的安全问题。近年来，约会公司已采取措施让用户安心，例如添加让公司拥有的工具对匹配对象<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tinder-adds-background-checks-to-its-dating-app-11646834400?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">进行背景调查的</a>选项。 Tinder 的母公司 Match Group 拒绝置评。</p><p> 《我们约会同一个人吗》的创始人保拉·桑切斯 (Paola Sanchez) 也描述了创建私人 Facebook 群组的类似原因。 “我最初创建这些小组是为了帮助解决我和我的朋友在约会时遇到的一些问题和危险，”她在 3 月份创建的 GoFundMe 页面上写道。 （该页面显示，桑切斯正在筹集资金，以开发一款“我们在约会同一个人吗？”风格的应用程序。根据她的 GoFundMe 数据，她已筹集了超过 44,000 美元。）在最近的更新中，她写道，她的群组也旨在成为寻求恋爱建议的空间，已经聚集了超过 230 万会员。桑切斯拒绝对本文发表评论。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="518" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-817716?width=700&amp;height=518" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCredit">插图：《华尔街日报》的埃里克·卡特。杂志</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据美国疾病控制与预防中心称，与“DontDateHimGirl”一样，“我们和同一个人约会吗”团体也面向异性恋女性，她们遭受<a href="https://www.cdc.gov/violenceprevention/sexualviolence/fastfact.html" target="_blank" class="icon none">性骚扰和暴力的</a>比例高于异性恋男性。</p><p>每个团体都列出了其成员必须同意的类似“搏击俱乐部”的冗长规则，因为它试图防止有关团体外男性的信息传播、人肉搜索（泄露地址等身份信息）以及违反 Facebook 的审核系统。</p><p>禁止对群内帖子进行截图。分享男性的姓氏、社交媒体账号、电话号码、地址或其他身份信息也是如此。另一条规则规定“不得诽谤、诽谤或侵犯版权”。</p><p>该指南指示会员在发帖时要包含“最少甚至没有细节”，并提供了诸如“有茶吗？”之类的示例。或“Joe 🚩🚩”并建议发帖人仅在评论中保留详细信息。 This allows moderators to swiftly approve posts without concern they may contain libel or otherwise run afoul of Facebook guidelines, which can jeopardize the group.</p><p> There&#39;s also a policy against judging a man&#39;s appearance or otherwise making fun of him. “This group is not about hating men,” the forums say in their “About Me” sections.</p><h3> &#39;Should I Look Him Up?&#39;</h3><p> Venus Sanchez, a 28-year-old in New York City, joined her local group last June. In the year that she&#39;s been a member, she was able to warn her friend that she was dating someone who&#39;d been accused of serial sexual harassment and discovered that she herself was being catfished—misled by a potential suitor about his identity.</p><p> For her, the group functions as an additional filter for the dating apps she uses, Bumble and Hinge. “If I match with someone, the first thing I think about is: Should I look him up on Are We Dating The Same Guy and see if he&#39;s, like, a psychopath?”她说。</p><p> Ashley Uzer, a 29-year-old copywriter based in Los Angeles, joined the city&#39;s group last fall out of curiosity. She saw a post about a guy she recognized from her Instagram DMs and decided to comment on it, describing the suggestive messages he&#39;d sent her.</p><p> “Someone sent him a screenshot of all the girls who&#39;d commented,” Uzer said. “He was like, &#39;I thought we were friends.&#39; It made me scared to post again.” She didn&#39;t want anyone else to find out if she&#39;d written about them.</p><p> She was surprised by how trivial many of the Facebook posts were. “Girls are commenting like every little experience they&#39;ve had with a guy and to be honest, I don&#39;t think a guy going out with you and not texting you after is tea—that&#39;s dating,” said Uzer.</p><p> The conversations happening in these private groups have moved beyond Facebook in recent months.</p><p> Posts with the hashtag #AreWeDatingTheSameGuy—or #AWDTSG for short—have garnered more than 19 million views on TikTok as dating experts muse on why they think the groups can be toxic, members gush over their entertainment value, and men warn others to be aware of their existence.</p><p> On Reddit, people are posting detailed instructions for how to send Meta takedown requests through a process for reporting misuse of copyright material, such as personal photos. A Meta spokesperson declined to comment. There are also groups trying to flip the script and ask: “Are We Dating the Same Girl?”</p><h3> New Groups, New Rules</h3><p> John Harden, a 37-year-old in Boston who runs a shipping company, said he started the private Facebook group “Are We Dating The Same Girl? Boston / Providence Edition” after learning about the original groups the hard way.</p><p> “Someone posted my picture and said &#39;any red flags or any tea&#39;?”他说。 “I was dating a little bit, but I wasn&#39;t in a relationship.”</p><p> When he tried to join the group to see whether people had commented on the post, “my request was rejected,” he said. “I decided to create my own.” Harden said most of the posts in his group are from men who want to find out if the women they&#39;re dating are seeing multiple men.</p><p> The experiences of straight men on dating apps differ from straight women and lesbian, gay or bisexual users, who are much more likely to receive unwanted sexually explicit messages or images on dating sites, according to a <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2023/02/02/from-looking-for-love-to-swiping-the-field-online-dating-in-the-u-s/" target="_blank" class="icon none">Pew Research survey</a> published in February. Straight men reported more encounters with potential scammers.</p><p> Harden&#39;s group and others like it say they are for men who want to warn about women who are liars, cheaters, scammers or exhibit “toxic or shady behavior.”</p><p> “If a guy goes on a date with a girl and she&#39;s known to maybe use guys to get a meal, or whatever, it may be important to share that,” said Harden. His group has roughly 750 members; a similar group for men dating in the Washington, DC, area has more than 7,000 members.</p><p> Some women have grown disenchanted with how the original Are We Dating the Same Guy groups are run. Ashley Benson, a 37-year-old in South Florida who used to moderate some of Sanchez&#39;s original groups, is an administrator of 15 Are We Dating The Same Guy: Uncensored groups on Facebook.</p><p> While the “uncensored” versions borrow many of the original groups&#39; posting rules, Benson said they allow women to comment more freely, without fear of being kicked out.</p><p> Of the original groups, she said, “You have to walk on eggshells over there with everything you say.”</p><p> Write to Sara Ashley O&#39;Brien at <a href="mailto:sara.obrien@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sara.obrien@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4> More in Style</h4><ul class="articleList"><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/mcdonalds-grimace-purple-milkshake-tiktok-6915d5c9?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">How McDonald&#39;s Turned Grimace Into TikTok Gold</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/private-chef-tiktok-hamptons-8c6b279a?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">In Miami, the Hamptons and Los Angeles, It&#39;s Private Chef Season</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jiu-jitsu-mark-zuckerberg-9aff7dc1?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Is That Zuck on the Mat? A-Listers Are Learning the Art of Combat</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ozempic-wegovy-weight-loss-body-positivity-marketing-6e918f8c?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Will Ozempic Change &#39;Body Positivity&#39; for Good?</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chatbots-banter-ai-forever-voices-f845e2ec?mod=article_relatedinline" target="_blank" class="icon none">&#39;Hi, It&#39;s Taylor Swift&#39;: How AI Is Using Famous Voices and Why It Matters</a></li></ul></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 14:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/are-we-dating-the-same-guy-facebook-groups-2c7d3009</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/are-we-dating-the-same-guy-facebook-groups-2c7d3009<author><![CDATA[Sara Ashley O’Brien]]></author><category>世界时尚</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台/工具</category><category>技术</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>人际关系</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>元平台</category><category>梅塔</category><category>Facebook</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>关系</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category><category>社交媒体平台</category><category>工具</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.K. Clinches $5 Billion EV-Battery Plant as Race for Green Investments Heats Up]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Move by Jaguar Land Rover owner Tata comes as Europe tries to attract more projects <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066091"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="587" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819833?width=860&amp;height=587" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Finished Range Rover cars are loaded on to a transporter at Tata&#39;s Jaguar Land Rover plant in the UK</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：克里斯·拉特克利夫/彭博新闻</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001066091"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/william-boston" itemprop="url" rel="author">威廉·波士顿</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">July 19, 2023 9:15 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-cinches-5-billion-ev-battery-plant-as-race-for-green-investments-heats-up-e20b142f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> The owner of Jaguar Land Rover plans to build a large battery factory in the UK to supply electric vehicles, throwing a lifeline to Britain&#39;s auto industry and highlighting the global race for green investment as carmakers shift to EVs.</p><p> Tata Group said Wednesday that it expects the plant to start delivering batteries in 2026 and supply future electric vehicles built by its JLR business, which makes Range Rover, Defender, Discovery and Jaguar cars. The Indian company said it was investing 4 billion pounds, equivalent to about $5.2 billion, in the project.</p><p> Tata&#39;s decision to build the factory in the UK comes as European governments compete for a slice of the billions of dollars that the automotive industry is investing in its shift toward electric vehicles.</p><p> Most EV batteries today are supplied by Asian manufacturers. Europe is now trying to catch up and promote the growth of a regional battery industry to secure technology and jobs, and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/vw-is-on-a-hunt-for-resources-to-remove-china-from-its-ev-batteries-663ee99?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">become less dependent on China.</a></p><p> The rivalry for green-tech investment—and the thousands of jobs that could come with it—has been exacerbated by the Biden administration&#39;s Inflation Reduction Act, which has attracted a number of battery projects to the US instead of Europe. That is prompting European governments to offer subsidies and other <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-sets-out-options-to-compete-with-u-s-green-subsidies-11675253742?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">incentives to lure EV and battery projects</a> .</p><p> “It&#39;s a competitive world, so everyone is trying to attract business to their shores,” Grant Shapps, the UK&#39;s energy security secretary, told BBC radio on Wednesday.</p><p> Tata had initially planned to build the plant elsewhere, Shapps said. He declined to elaborate on the amount of incentives and other financial details included in the UK&#39;s winning bid for the plant, but said: “It is large, make no bones about that.”</p><p> The British government said the planned Tata factory was a boost to the country&#39;s automotive sector that would create up to 4,000 new direct jobs, and thousands more in the wider supply chain.</p><p> Sales of fully electric vehicles in the UK rose to 152,965 in the first half of the year, an increase of 33% from a year ago, according to the European Automobile Manufacturers&#39; Association. That outpaced the 18% growth in sales of all types of vehicles during the same period.</p><p> Faraday Institution, a UK-based research institute for battery technology, has estimated that Britain&#39;s auto industry would need up to 10 large battery-cell manufacturing plants by 2040 to secure the country&#39;s place in the global EV economy.</p><p> The UK&#39;s record in winning battery investment has been patchy.</p><p> Battery startup Britishvolt fell into administration after failing to secure sufficient cash to continue operations. The failure of Britishvolt was a stark warning for the UK government, analysts said, and increased the urgency of clinching Tata&#39;s investment.</p><p> Other European countries have also been struggling to maintain investment flows into new battery manufacturing in the wake of hefty US subsidies.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/XE/XETR/VOW" class="company-name">Volkswagen</a> earlier this year put <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/volkswagen-pivots-to-north-america-as-europe-loses-its-shine-1f26d7e5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">plans to build a battery plant in Eastern Europe on hold</a> to build a plant in Canada instead. Freyr Battery, an NYSE-listed company that is building a battery factory in Norway, abandoned starting a second European project to tap US aid to expand there instead.</p><p>写信给威廉·波士顿<a href="mailto:william.boston@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">william.boston@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 13:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/uk-cinches-5-billion-ev-battery-plant-as-race-for-green-investments-heats-up-e20b142f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/uk-cinches-5-billion-ev-battery-plant-as-race-for-green-investments-heats-up-e20b142f<author><![CDATA[William Boston]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>机动车</category><category>Passenger Cars</category><category> Sports Utility Vehicles</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>机动车零件</category><category>Diversified Holding Companies</category><category>汽车</category><category>Business/Consumer Services</category><category>企业战略/规划</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>Capital Expenditure</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>企业环境责任</category><category>环境/社会/治理</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> corporate strategy</category><category>规划</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>capital expenditure</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>企业环境责任</category><category>环境的</category><category>社会的</category><category>治理</category><category>机动车</category><category>passenger cars</category><category> sports utility vehicles</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>机动车辆零件</category><category>diversified holding companies</category><category>汽车</category><category>商业</category><category>consumer services </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Venture Firms’ China Tech Deals Investigated by Congress Panel]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> House select committee says American firms&#39; investments contributed to China&#39;s military buildup and rights abuses <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065586"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819660?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Reps. Mike Gallagher, seated, and Raja Krishnamoorthi lead the House Select Committee on the Chinese Communist Party.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Tom Williams/CQ Roll Call/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001065586"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/kate-okeeffe" itemprop="url" rel="author">Kate O&#39;Keeffe</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/berber-jin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Berber Jin</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 19, 2023 9:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-venture-firms-deals-in-china-tech-investigated-by-congress-panel-710addc8"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> A clutch of American venture-capital firms are being investigated by a congressional committee over their funding of Chinese tech companies—part of a push in Washington <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/thechinahawkin-washington-rattling-corporate-boardrooms-a9c10117?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to scrutinize and potentially ban</a> such deals.</p><p> The <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/house-committee-lays-out-case-for-china-threat-ad62c611?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">House&#39;s select committee on the China threat</a> this week notified GGV Capital, GSR Ventures, Walden International and Qualcomm Ventures—the investment arm of chip company <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/QCOM" class="company-name">Qualcomm</a> —that the panel is examining many of their investments in Chinese companies involved in semiconductors, artificial intelligence and quantum computing.</p><p> Those Chinese companies, the committee said, threaten US national security and have been involved in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-warns-businesses-over-supply-chains-tied-to-rights-violations-in-china-11593625904" target="_blank" class="icon none">human-rights violations</a> . By extension, the American firms&#39; investments “directly contribute” to those human-rights abuses, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-military-spending-growth-to-accelerate-to-7-2-this-year-19703002" target="_blank" class="icon none">China&#39;s military modernization</a> and its effort to supplant US technological leadership, according to letters sent to the venture firms and reviewed by The Wall Street Journal.</p><p> GSR said the partners who worked on the deals in question are no longer at the firm. GGV declined to comment, while the other two firms didn&#39;t immediately respond to requests for comment.</p><p> Set up this year and formally known as the Select Committee on the Chinese Communist Party, the committee is increasingly targeting the role of American businesses in abetting <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-has-a-new-vision-for-itself-global-power-da8dc559" target="_blank" class="icon none">Beijing&#39;s superpower ambitions</a> . Its work is emblematic of a shift in thinking in the White House and on Capitol Hill that once supported US business ties with China but now <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-investment-flows-to-silicon-valley-venture-funds-11663234202?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">see some investment</a> as counter to American interests.</p><p> Especially problematic are investments that may help China develop technology that could end up being used against the US in a potential military conflict or assist Beijing in building its surveillance state.</p><p> “We shouldn&#39;t be funding our own destruction,” the panel&#39;s chairman, Republican Rep. Mike Gallagher of Wisconsin, said in an interview. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="452" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819661?width=700&amp;height=452" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Sequoia Capital drew the ire of Washington hawks because of a series of Chinese tech investments made by its China unit.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Josh Edelson/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The committee&#39;s top Democrat, Rep. Raja Krishnamoorthi of Illinois, said that American money and expertise shouldn&#39;t be used to enable China&#39;s “advancements in the technologies that could undermine our national security or American values.”</p><p> While the committee doesn&#39;t have lawmaking authority, it does have subpoena powers. Gallagher said the goal of the investigation is to compile a record that would help Congress pass a strong bill to restrict problematic investment in China.</p><p> The Senate is discussing an amendment filed by Sens. Bob Casey (D., Pa.) and John Cornyn (R., Texas) to a must-pass defense-policy bill that would require US investors to file notice of their investments in certain companies in China and other adversary nations. The White House is also working on an executive order on screening outbound investment in certain sectors.</p><p> Both the proposed Senate amendment and the executive order have been subject to lobbying from the business community, according to people involved in the process. As a result, the amendment lacks an earlier version&#39;s mechanism to review or block such investments.</p><p> The select committee, in its letters, gave the venture firms, all of them based in California, until July 26 to respond.</p><p> The letters called out GGV and Qualcomm Ventures for having invested in Megvii Technology and</p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HK/XHKG/20" class="">SenseTime</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> respectively. Those artificial-intelligence companies, which provide facial-recognition technology, are among 28 Chinese entities the Trump administration placed on an export blacklist in 2019, citing their roles in assisting Beijing&#39;s repression of Muslim minorities in the Xinjiang region.<p></p><p> The committee also cites in its letters Walden&#39;s investment in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/HK/XHKG/981?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Semiconductor Manufacturing International</a> Corp., or SMIC, China&#39;s largest chip maker. The US in 2020 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-blacklists-chinas-top-chip-maker-escalating-tech-fight-11608274932?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">restricted exports to SMIC</a> because of its support for the Chinese military. GSR was cited for investments in artificial intelligence and semiconductor companies.</p><p> The Chinese tech companies didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment. The Chinese embassy in Washington said “the US has politicized and weaponized economic and technological issues, seriously violating the principles of market economy.” It criticized the select committee for “spreading the &#39;China threat&#39; theory and making slanderous attacks on Communist Party of China.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="438" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819662?width=700&amp;height=438" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> SenseTime, which provides facial-recognition technology, was among 28 Chinese entities placed on an export blacklist by the Trump administration in 2019.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Cfoto/NurPhoto/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The information the committee is seeking from the venture firms includes details of the Chinese companies they have invested in, management advice they have given and the role of the Communist Party in the companies.</p><p> Gallagher said this venture-capital probe is the first of a series of investigations that the committee plans to conduct into the relationships between the investment world and the party. A future target, Gallagher said, is <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AU/XASX/SEQ" class="company-name">Sequoia</a> Capital.</p><p> Sequoia, a venture-capital icon for investments in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">Apple</a> and TikTok owner ByteDance, drew the ire of Washington China hawks because of a series of Chinese tech investments made by its China unit. Following <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sequoia-made-a-fortune-investing-in-the-u-s-and-china-then-it-had-to-pick-one-f13e7b91?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">two years of scrutiny</a> from the White House and Capitol Hill, Sequoia in June said that the firm would break up into separate independent entities for the US, China and other areas.</p><p> While the move could insulate Sequoia&#39;s US arm from Washington policy debates, it doesn&#39;t preclude major US institutional investors from continuing to invest their money in Chinese tech companies through the Sequoia China spinoff.</p><p> Gallagher said, despite the split, he still has unanswered questions about Sequoia&#39;s decision to break up as well as its current operations.</p><p> Write to Kate O&#39;Keeffe at <a href="mailto:kathryn.okeeffe@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">kathryn.okeeffe@wsj.com</a> and Berber Jin at <a href="mailto:berber.jin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">berber.jin@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 13:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-venture-firms-deals-in-china-tech-investigated-by-congress-panel-710addc8</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-venture-firms-deals-in-china-tech-investigated-by-congress-panel-710addc8<author><![CDATA[Kate O’KeeffeBerber Jin]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>Trusts/Funds/Financial Vehicles</category><category>私人产权</category><category>Alternative Investments</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资/证券</category><category>Venture Capital</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Sequoia Capital</category><category> SEQCAP.XX</category><category> Qualcomm</category><category> QCOM</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>trusts</category><category> funds</category><category> financial vehicles</category><category> private equity</category><category> alternative investments</category><category>金融服务</category><category>投资</category><category>证券</category><category>venture capital </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Business, Labor Square Off Over AI’s Future in American Workplace]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> ChatGPT investigation by FTC could be test of US authority to regulate AI <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064457"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819257?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Federal Trade Commission is asking questions about OpenAI&#39;s policies for selling access to its AI systems.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Eric Lee for The Wall Street Journal </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064457"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-tracy" itemprop="url" rel="author">Ryan Tracy</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 19, 2023 8:44 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/business-and-labor-square-off-over-ais-future-in-american-workplace-add9e41"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> WASHINGTON—The Federal Trade Commission&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chatgpt-under-investigation-by-ftc-21e4b3ef?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">investigation into the ChatGPT app</a> points to an emerging conflict over how Washington should regulate artificial intelligence, one that could pit some of America&#39;s biggest businesses against labor unions and progressive advocacy groups.</p><p> Businesses want to use systems like ChatGPT, which can instantly generate media and imitate human conversation, to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-jobs-most-exposed-to-chatgpt-e7ceebf0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">cut the number of employees</a> needed to write documents or answer calls. AI-driven bots could also open up new markets by creating individually customized ads or even pitching customers in live conversation.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Labor unions, privacy advocates and consumer groups see AI&#39;s potential benefits, too. But they fear that AI will eliminate jobs and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ai-promised-to-make-jobs-easier-workers-werent-so-sure-4ace9ddd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">downgrade working conditions</a> . If an AI system were trained to persuade, bad actors could feed it a person&#39;s private data and use it to manipulate or defraud, some warn.</p><p>现在， <em>&nbsp;</em> as the US government takes its first tentative steps <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-developing-national-ai-strategy-ee22b44e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">toward regulating AI</a> , the Biden administration&#39;s close ties to labor and progressive groups has some in business and tech concerned that the regulatory push will go too far, by stunting the development and use of a technology seen as crucial to powering the US economy in the future.</p><p> Those fears were stoked by disclosure last week of the FTC probe of ChatGPT creator OpenAI. The agency is asking detailed questions about OpenAI&#39;s policies for selling access to its AI systems to other businesses, among other topics.</p><p> “The regulatory uncertainty and overreach that could come with such an approach would significantly hamstring America&#39;s ability to compete and deploy societally beneficial uses of AI,” said Jordan Crenshaw, a senior vice president at the US Chamber of Commerce.</p><p> How businesses and consumers can harness the benefits while avoiding abuses of the powerful technology is at the heart of the regulatory debate. OpenAI&#39;s GPT and other so-called <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chatgpt-ai-chatbot-app-explained-11675865177?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">generative AI systems</a> could power virtual agents tuned to the desires of specific individuals, with the ability to converse with humans in real time, upending how Americans work, shop and travel. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=839822A9-3A5F-4A5D-9390-E94EDF4A2336&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fbusiness-and-labor-square-off-over-ais-future-in-american-workplace-add9e41&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">人工智能在白领工作中发挥着越来越重要的作用，能够起草电子邮件、演示文稿、图像等。插图：雅各布·雷诺兹<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>“Throughout our digital lives, we will just talk to our computers,” Louis Rosenberg, chief executive of AI developer Unanimous AI, said at a recent conference hosted by the advocacy group Public Citizen.</p><p> That will create opportunities for businesses to exercise “targeted, customized, influence at scale,” Rosenberg said. But if left unregulated, such a tool “could be the most dangerous technology for human manipulation that we&#39;ve had to confront,” he added.</p><p> The FTC hasn&#39;t said it intends to write a broad AI regulation. In drafting both a national strategy on AI and recommendations for “accountability measures,” Biden administration officials have repeatedly said they want to strike a balance between fostering innovation and preventing harm.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>How should AI be regulated?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> Labor is a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-puts-union-support-at-center-of-agenda-11639231201?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">key constituency of the Biden administration,</a> and union representatives met with White House officials July 3 to articulate their concerns.</p><p> Unions are concerned not only about job losses, but about companies using AI applications to keep tabs on workers outside of their jobs, where an AI-driven system might identify a group of workers carrying their employer-issued smartphones to a union organizing meeting, according to Amanda Ballantyne,</p> director of AFL-CIO&#39;s technology institute.<p></p><p> “You hear stories from workers about having their time in the bathroom tracked,” she said.</p><p> Civil-rights groups are also concerned about racial or gender bias creeping into business decisions when companies use AI as a sort of automated consultant, a practice that is growing in fields such as healthcare, recruitment and finance.</p><p> Some of these groups pushed successfully for a New York City law that <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-york-city-delays-enforcement-of-ai-bias-law-11670966590?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">requires bias audits</a> of the AI-driven systems that many companies now use to find recruits for job openings.</p><p> Similar regulatory ideas are gaining traction in Washington. Earlier this year, an arm of the Commerce Department sought comments on <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-weighs-possible-rules-for-ai-tools-like-chatgpt-46f8257b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">possible accountability measures</a> for AI systems, including whether potentially risky new AI models should go through a certification process before they are released. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819281?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Auditing firm PwC filed a comment with the Commerce Department praising the benefits of third-party audits.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Richard B. Levine/Levine Roberts/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “Whatever guardrails are set around AI, it needs to work not just for the largest players but the entire ecosystem,” said Doug Johnson, a vice president at the Consumer Technology Association, a trade group that represents more than 1,000 tech companies of various sizes.</p><p> The Blue Cross Blue Shield Association, a group of health insurers that consistently ranks among Washington&#39;s top lobbying spenders, told the Commerce Department that officials should consider the costs to businesses before adopting a requirement that major or high-risk AI systems be audited by a third party.</p><p> Third-party audits can be “resource-intensive, difficult to obtain, and often cost-prohibitive,” the group wrote.</p><p> On the other side of the ledger, auditing giant PwC filed a comment praising the benefits of audits, which the company itself might be retained to conduct. “We know that information that is subject to third-party assurance garners more trust,” PwC wrote.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">Microsoft</a> and OpenAI have called on the US to develop a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chatgpts-sam-altman-faces-senate-panel-examining-artificial-intelligence-4bb6942a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">new AI regulatory program</a> , including by setting up a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsofts-president-backs-new-agency-to-regulate-chatgpt-other-ai-systems-c847bae0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">new federal agency</a> to license powerful AI systems.</p><p> That sentiment isn&#39;t shared by everyone in the tech industry. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819284?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Google has said it opposes a new &#39;Department of AI.&#39;</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: David Paul Morris/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GOOG" class="">Alphabet</a> <span class="company-name-type">&#39;s</span> Google, which offers AI systems that compete with Microsoft and OpenAI, said in its comment that it opposes a new “Department of AI” and favors instead “a hub-and-spoke approach—with a central agency like the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) informing sectoral regulators” overseeing specific industries. NIST recently published a voluntary framework for managing AI risks.</p><p> “AI is too important not to regulate,” Google said, but it added: “Any new regulations should avoid impairing the operation of systems that deliver significant value for Americans.”</p><p> Besides the Commerce Department effort, both Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (D., NY) and the White House&#39;s Office of Science and Technology Policy have launched efforts to gather public input in the name of shaping future rules.</p><p> That sets up what is expected to be a fresh gold mine for Washington lobbyists.</p><p> “Some of the largest companies in America getting involved in the AI debate means that a lot more money and influence is going to get thrown around,” said Adam Thierer, a senior fellow on technology and innovation at the R Street Institute think tank. “There is now a cacophony of voices to hear from.”</p><p> Write to Ryan Tracy at <a href="mailto:ryan.tracy@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.tracy@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/45b711d0-d12b-4ed4-89ff-24783c6b1fa4.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 12:44:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/business-and-labor-square-off-over-ais-future-in-american-workplace-add9e41</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/business-and-labor-square-off-over-ais-future-in-american-workplace-add9e41<author><![CDATA[Ryan Tracy]]></author><category>人工智能技术</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>人工智能/机器学习</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>一般劳工问题</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>人工智能</category><category>机器学习</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>一般劳工问题</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>人工智能技术</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tesla to Report Second-Quarter Earnings Fueled by Sales Growth]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Analysts are looking to see the impact of price cuts on EV maker&#39;s bottom line <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064705"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="572" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818428?width=860&amp;height=572" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> So far this year, Tesla has cut starting prices across its lineup by between 14% and 28% in the US</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: David Paul Morris/Bloomberg News </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001064705"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/rebecca-elliott" itemprop="url" rel="author">Rebecca Elliott</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 19, 2023 5:30 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q2-earnings-report-2023-9be2b571"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> After a rocky start to the year, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TSLA" class="company-name">Tesla</a> has returned to a feverish <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-deliveries-to-show-whether-price-cuts-are-paying-off-2f2aac93?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">rate of sales growth</a> for its electric vehicles. That growth&#39;s cost will become evident Wednesday when the company reports second-quarter financial results.</p><p> New-vehicle deliveries almost doubled in the April-through-June period to a record high. Still, analysts expect profit to rise just 3.4% from a year earlier after the Texas-based automaker slashed US prices by more than a fifth on some offerings.</p><p> Tesla&#39;s automotive gross margin, a closely watched measure of profitability, is expected to narrow to its lowest level in almost six years at a time when the company is preparing to boost spending to ramp up <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-begins-cybertruck-production-after-yearslong-wait-dbff33f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">production of the Cybertruck</a> . <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p> Investors have regained <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-leads-surge-in-battered-clean-energy-stocks-e805be58?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">enthusiasm for the stock,</a> even as Tesla confronts slowing profit growth and increased costs from expansion.</p><p> Tesla shares have more than doubled this year through Tuesday <strong>,</strong> after starting 2023 down amid jitters about whether demand was waning for its vehicles. There also was uncertainty around Chief Executive <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/elon-musk">Elon Musk</a> &#39;s focus on the carmaker after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/story/twitter-purchased-by-elon-musk-how-it-went-down-72a07de3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">buying social-media company Twitter</a> late last year.</p><p> Those qualms appear to have eased since he <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/linda-yaccarino-new-twitter-ceo-42a4f206#?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">appointed a Twitter CEO</a> to run day-to-day operations and reported earlier this month that Tesla&#39;s second-quarter deliveries had surged 83%. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=467C2608-5C54-438F-ADA5-8E7477A8A49D&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Ftesla-tsla-q2-earnings-report-2023-9be2b571&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> At Tesla&#39;s shareholder meeting in May, CEO Elon Musk forecast a challenging year ahead for the carmaker. Photo: Jay Janner/Austin American-Statesman/AP<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>Investors on Wednesday will be looking for the company to indicate how heavily it <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-subtle-strategy-behind-elon-musks-price-cuts-at-tesla-180a3036?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">will lean on discounts</a> in the second half.</p><p> Plans to adopt Tesla&#39;s EV charging technology, announced in recent months <strong>&nbsp;</strong> by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GM" class="">General Motors</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/F" class="company-name">Ford Motor</a> and other automakers, have also helped highlight Musk&#39;s advantages in the EV market, especially as rivals show signs of swelling inventory. On Monday, Ford slashed the starting price of its <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-cuts-price-of-ev-f-150-lightning-truck-by-up-to-17-2cc21c6a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">EV pickup, the F-150 Lightning,</a> by almost $10,000.</p><p> The cut, along with falling prices more generally for EVs, has raised broader questions about the strength of demand for battery-powered cars as more companies expand their factory output. Some analysts are skeptical that they have seen the end of price cuts by Tesla.</p><p> Musk has said he is chasing growth at the expense of profitability, betting the move will pay long-term dividends for the world&#39;s top seller of EVs. The company has targeted production growth of 31% this year while Musk has suggested closer to 50% is possible.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> The cost to its bottom line should be evident Wednesday. Analysts surveyed by FactSet, on average, predict Tesla will report a $2.3 billion profit in the second quarter, off revenue that rose to $24.2 billion.</p><p> So far this year, Tesla has cut starting prices across its lineup by between 14% and 28% in the US, depending on the model, according to The Wall Street Journal&#39;s review of the changes on Tesla&#39;s website.</p><p> Analysts such as</p> Toni Sacconaghi of Bernstein Research expect Tesla to report its lowest automotive gross margin, excluding money made from selling regulatory credits, since 2017, when the company was struggling to increase production of the Model 3 sedan.<p></p><p> That closely watched figure was 26% in the second quarter of 2022, while Sacconaghi expects this past quarter&#39;s margin to have narrowed to about 16%.</p><p> In April, Chief Financial Officer Zach Kirkhorn cautioned investors against “reading too much into” Tesla&#39;s margins in the near term.</p><p> “What happens to margins over the next couple of quarters only matters in the context of what that means for our ability to reinvest into 2024 and 2025,” Kirkhorn said. “We have a lot of space before that becomes something that we have to revisit—our investment plans.”</p><p> The company has signaled it <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/teslas-growth-ambition-comes-with-a-175-billion-price-tag-55b7e4d4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">is going on a spending spree</a> in coming years as it seeks to boost production capacity to handle making 20 million vehicles annually by 2030. Last year, it made about 1.37 million vehicles.</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Over the weekend, Tesla said it had begun building the Cybertruck, a sci-fi-inspired pickup, at its Texas assembly plant outside Austin. Tesla also has sought approval to <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-outlines-plan-to-create-largest-auto-factory-in-germany-4aaea3bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">double the size of its factory</a> near Berlin to produce up to one million cars a year, and it has announced plans for a new assembly plant in Mexico.</p><p> So far, Tesla has said it aims to fund its expansion with cash generated from the business.</p><p> Tesla&#39;s free cash flow fell 80% in the first quarter to $441 million, from $2.2 billion a year earlier. That was its worst generation of free cash since the second quarter of 2020, when the company was struggling with Covid-19-related shutdowns and ramping up production of the Model Y crossover.</p><p> Write to Rebecca Elliott at <a href="mailto:rebecca.elliott@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">rebecca.elliott@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/d90969df-db3f-4890-9f4e-2892f502493a.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q2-earnings-report-2023-9be2b571</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/tesla-tsla-q2-earnings-report-2023-9be2b571<author><![CDATA[Rebecca Elliott]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>corpearnings</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>收益</category><category>销售数据</category><category>Earnings Surprises</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>特斯拉</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>财务绩效</category><category>earnings</category><category>销售数据</category><category>earnings surprises</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>机动车</category><category>替代燃料汽车</category><category>汽车</category></item></channel></rss>